00:52:39,634 --> 00:52:40,940
I can't.

1077
00:52:41,070 --> 00:52:43,334
I'm not pretending
to understand your grief.

1078
00:52:43,464 --> 00:52:46,337
God knows, if my husband
was in a coma for a month,

1079
00:52:46,467 --> 00:52:47,947
I couldn't leave my house!

1080
00:52:50,036 --> 00:52:52,647
But I am not an artist,
Nicky, and you are.

1081
00:52:52,778 --> 00:52:54,649
And the way that
artists deal with life,

1082
00:52:54,780 --> 00:52:56,695
the good and the bad,
is through their art.

1083
00:52:59,872 --> 00:53:03,354
George wouldn't want
you to stop painting.

1084
00:53:03,484 --> 00:53:05,573
No matter what.

1085
00:53:05,704 --> 00:53:07,401
Honour him with your gift.

1086
00:53:13,842 --> 00:53:15,104
Bye.

1087
00:53:34,036 --> 00:53:35,516
Finished up the bedrooms

1088
00:53:35,647 --> 00:53:37,692
at the top floor
of the servants' quarters.

1089
00:53:37,823 --> 00:53:39,259
Thanks, Peter.

1090
00:53:39,390 --> 00:53:41,261
You didn't have to do that.

1091
00:53:43,002 --> 00:53:44,960
Well, it's no big deal.

1092
00:53:47,049 --> 00:53:50,314
I really wish you'd let me
pay you for your work, Peter.

1093
00:53:50,444 --> 00:53:51,793
Not a chance.

1094
00:53:51,924 --> 00:53:53,317
You gonna finish it?

1095
00:53:54,666 --> 00:53:55,884
I don't know yet.

1096
00:53:56,015 --> 00:53:59,105
Well, for what it's worth,
I think you should.

1097
00:53:59,236 --> 00:54:02,500
It'll only raise the value of
the place when you do resell it.

1098
00:54:14,425 --> 00:54:15,687
[ Nicky sighs ]

1099
00:54:23,347 --> 00:54:24,391
[ Moans ]

1100
00:54:38,710 --> 00:54:39,754
[ Chuckles ]

1101
00:54:59,034 --> 00:55:00,209
What is that?

1102
00:55:32,154 --> 00:55:33,155
[ Sighs ]

1103
00:55:36,811 --> 00:55:37,899
[ Sighs ]

1104
00:57:16,563 --> 00:57:17,651
My God!

1105
00:57:20,524 --> 00:57:22,439
This is from the 1800s.

1106
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:28,445
[ Sighs ]

1107
00:57:31,970 --> 00:57:33,188
[ Sighs ]

1108
00:57:43,764 --> 00:57:44,809
What is this?

1109
00:57:48,987 --> 00:57:50,336
 No, no, no 

1110
00:57:53,339 --> 00:57:54,253
[ Phone ringing ]

1111
00:57:55,820 --> 00:57:57,691
Wait, Peter. I'll get it.

1112
00:57:57,822 --> 00:57:59,519
 No, no, no 

1113
00:58:05,438 --> 00:58:06,613
It's Nicky.

1114
00:58:08,006 --> 00:58:09,747
Your timing really sucks, Nicky!

1115
00:58:09,877 --> 00:58:12,358
It's not too late
to call, is it?

1116
00:58:12,489 --> 00:58:14,926
Uh, actually, 5 minutes
later would have been better.

1117
00:58:15,056 --> 00:58:16,144
What's up?

1118
00:58:16,275 --> 00:58:18,103
Well...

1119
00:58:18,233 --> 00:58:20,061
I'm in Maine, on the island.

1120
00:58:21,323 --> 00:58:23,282
I decided to finish the retreat.

1121
00:58:23,412 --> 00:58:25,937
Uh... are you sure
that's a good idea?

1122
00:58:26,067 --> 00:58:27,721
No.

1123
00:58:27,852 --> 00:58:30,202
But I think I needed it somehow.

1124
00:58:32,204 --> 00:58:33,379
Anyway, I just...

1125
00:58:33,510 --> 00:58:35,163
I really wanted to talk to you,

1126
00:58:35,294 --> 00:58:37,339
and I'm gonna be
in Boston tomorrow,

1127
00:58:37,470 --> 00:58:39,777
and I was hoping that
we could do breakfast.

1128
00:58:39,907 --> 00:58:41,909
Um... how about, um, lunch?

1129
00:58:42,040 --> 00:58:43,650
I'm gonna be working late.

1130
00:58:43,781 --> 00:58:45,609
Yeah. The caf, 2:00?

1131
00:58:45,739 --> 00:58:47,698
Sounds good!
See you tomorrow!

1132
00:58:47,828 --> 00:58:49,264
Hmm!

1133
00:58:49,395 --> 00:58:51,615
Now, don't make
a liar out of me.

1134
00:58:52,746 --> 00:58:53,965
[ Giggling ]

1135
00:59:05,716 --> 00:59:07,631
Everything looks all right.

1136
00:59:07,761 --> 00:59:09,763
We'll see what the
blood tests turn up,

1137
00:59:09,894 --> 00:59:12,287
but at this point,
I wouldn't worry about it.

1138
00:59:12,418 --> 00:59:15,160
I have never gotten dizzy
like that before, Doctor Burke.

1139
00:59:15,290 --> 00:59:16,640
You're under a lot of stress,

1140
00:59:16,770 --> 00:59:18,772
which is normal, considering

1141
00:59:18,903 --> 00:59:19,860
George's condition.

1142
00:59:19,991 --> 00:59:21,383
Have you been eating regularly?

1143
00:59:23,516 --> 00:59:24,561
Yeah, not really.

1144
00:59:24,691 --> 00:59:26,954
Hmm. Why don't we start there.

1145
00:59:27,085 --> 00:59:29,740
Three meals. Daily vitamin.

1146
00:59:29,870 --> 00:59:31,698
Take it easy, and I'll call you

1147
00:59:31,829 --> 00:59:34,396
when I get the results
of your blood work.

1148
00:59:37,530 --> 00:59:39,619
I found it in this creepy room,

1149
00:59:39,750 --> 00:59:41,186
hidden behind a stone wall.

1150
00:59:41,316 --> 00:59:42,404
What is it?

1151
00:59:42,535 --> 00:59:43,580
I'm not sure,

1152
00:59:43,710 --> 00:59:45,843
but I'm gonna take it
to Prof. Shockley.

1153
00:59:45,973 --> 00:59:49,368
I'm pretty sure that it belonged
to George's distant grandfather,

1154
00:59:49,498 --> 00:59:51,239
the one that built
the summer house.

1155
00:59:51,370 --> 00:59:54,025
And I found it with this glass
plate negative of a woman.

1156
00:59:54,155 --> 00:59:55,461
It must be over 100 years old.

1157
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:56,810
And look at this.

1158
00:59:59,857 --> 01:00:02,424
Mmm, it's sweet!

1159
01:00:02,555 --> 01:00:04,992
You know what?
I remember taking this.

1160
01:00:05,123 --> 01:00:07,038
Margie, look close.
Behind me and George.

1161
01:00:09,649 --> 01:00:11,738
What? Creepy little room?

1162
01:00:11,869 --> 01:00:13,522
No. Look at the
shadow behind us.

1163
01:00:13,653 --> 01:00:15,873
Doesn't it look like a shape?

1164
01:00:16,003 --> 01:00:18,005
Like there's a person
standing behind us?

1165
01:00:18,136 --> 01:00:20,268
No. All I see is a room.

1166
01:00:30,844 --> 01:00:32,280
It's a shipping ledger.

1167
01:00:32,411 --> 01:00:33,586
Mm-hmm.

1168
01:00:33,717 --> 01:00:35,370
So what exactly is it used for?

1169
01:00:35,501 --> 01:00:37,895
It's the way a ship's captain

1170
01:00:38,025 --> 01:00:40,158
kept track of his
shipping transactions.

1171
01:00:40,288 --> 01:00:42,290
The list of items are logged

1172
01:00:42,421 --> 01:00:45,859
under the date
they're acquired here.

1173
01:00:45,990 --> 01:00:47,948
This is where it
was paid for, here.

1174
01:00:48,079 --> 01:00:49,646
The number of the item,

1175
01:00:49,776 --> 01:00:51,735
and the location
where it was purchased.

1176
01:00:51,865 --> 01:00:53,432
So these dates, 1854-1855,

1177
01:00:53,562 --> 01:00:56,348
those were the actual
dates that they were written?

1178
01:00:56,478 --> 01:00:59,394
Well, assuming it's
authentic, and it appears to be.

1179
01:00:59,525 --> 01:01:01,396
Have you read through
the whole ledger?

1180
01:01:01,527 --> 01:01:02,702
No, I haven't.

1181
01:01:02,833 --> 01:01:05,662
Ah. Well, it's in
incredible shape.

1182
01:01:05,792 --> 01:01:07,968
Well, I found it in
a sealed strongbox.

1183
01:01:08,099 --> 01:01:09,013
Ah, OK.

1184
01:01:09,143 --> 01:01:10,536
Look at this.

1185
01:01:10,667 --> 01:01:12,669
Oftentimes, this type of captain

1186
01:01:12,799 --> 01:01:14,975
would make log notes
in the ledger like this.

1187
01:01:15,106 --> 01:01:16,760
"High winds made for

1188
01:01:16,890 --> 01:01:19,371
"a quicker turn around the horn.

1189
01:01:19,501 --> 01:01:22,461
"Lost crewman Joyce
to a bout of scurvy."

1190
01:01:22,591 --> 01:01:23,723
Not exactly Hemingway,

1191
01:01:23,854 --> 01:01:26,030
but it might make for
some interesting reading.

1192
01:01:26,160 --> 01:01:29,598
And there may also be
some monetary value to it,

1193
01:01:29,729 --> 01:01:31,775
based on the history
it's documenting.

1194
01:01:31,905 --> 01:01:32,906
Mmm.

1195
01:01:35,561 --> 01:01:36,649
Oh my God.

1196
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:38,172
What's wrong?

1197
01:01:41,132 --> 01:01:42,437
Prof. Shockley,

1198
01:01:42,568 --> 01:01:44,309
please tell me
I'm reading this wrong.

1199
01:01:46,441 --> 01:01:48,139
No, you're not reading it wrong.

1200
01:01:48,269 --> 01:01:50,619
And I don't think
there's any question

1201
01:01:50,750 --> 01:01:52,796
that it's of
historical value now.

1202
01:01:52,926 --> 01:01:54,493
Does your husband
know about this?

1203
01:01:56,321 --> 01:01:57,670
N-no!

1204
01:01:58,845 --> 01:02:00,804
No, I don't...

1205
01:02:00,934 --> 01:02:03,850
I think he would
have told me if he knew

1206
01:02:03,981 --> 01:02:06,853
that his family was...
buying and selling slaves.

1207
01:02:11,597 --> 01:02:13,251
There's no way he
could have known.

1208
01:02:13,381 --> 01:02:14,513
Selling slaves is not

1209
01:02:14,643 --> 01:02:16,558
something George would
have kept from you.

1210
01:02:16,689 --> 01:02:18,038
I know.

1211
01:02:18,169 --> 01:02:20,519
It was a secret that
Jebidiah tried to bury,

1212
01:02:20,649 --> 01:02:22,564
and that's why it was
hidden in this wall.

1213
01:02:26,481 --> 01:02:28,048
George didn't know.

1214
01:02:31,399 --> 01:02:32,749
But maybe someone did.

1215
01:02:35,490 --> 01:02:38,058
What if the legend of
this house being haunted

1216
01:02:38,189 --> 01:02:40,104
is somehow tied
to Jebidiah's secret?

1217
01:02:43,803 --> 01:02:45,239
The glass negative.

1218
01:02:45,370 --> 01:02:46,893
What?

1219
01:02:48,547 --> 01:02:50,288
Remember? I told you
about it in Boston.

1220
01:02:50,418 --> 01:02:51,680
Yeah.

1221
01:02:51,811 --> 01:02:53,813
What if the person
in that glass negative

1222
01:02:53,944 --> 01:02:56,598
is somehow tied to the spirit
that's haunting this house?

1223
01:02:56,729 --> 01:02:58,775
I need to make a print of it.

1224
01:02:58,905 --> 01:03:01,821
I haven't seen
one of these in decades!

1225
01:03:01,952 --> 01:03:03,649
Where did you get it?

1226
01:03:03,780 --> 01:03:05,607
I found it at the summer house.

1227
01:03:05,738 --> 01:03:07,784
Do you know who it is?

1228
01:03:07,914 --> 01:03:10,569
No, I was hoping that
maybe you could tell me that.

1229
01:03:10,699 --> 01:03:13,354
Can you make a print
off of something this old?

1230
01:03:13,485 --> 01:03:16,575
I guess. It's a bit tricky,
but I've done it before.

1231
01:03:16,705 --> 01:03:18,533
I should have a few by tomorrow.

1232
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:23,016
I found a ledger that indicates

1233
01:03:23,147 --> 01:03:25,627
that Jebidiah Wickersham was
buying and selling slaves.

1234
01:03:25,758 --> 01:03:27,455
Oh, my lands!

1235
01:03:27,586 --> 01:03:30,502
Now, my instincts tell me
that it's all tied to the curse.

1236
01:03:30,632 --> 01:03:32,330
I know this sounds weird,

1237
01:03:32,460 --> 01:03:35,681
and I haven't told anyone,
not even my best friend Margie,

1238
01:03:35,812 --> 01:03:38,249
but I feel like the curse
has a hold of George.

1239
01:03:38,379 --> 01:03:40,817
That doesn't sound weird at all.

1240
01:03:40,947 --> 01:03:42,949
I feel like

1241
01:03:43,080 --> 01:03:45,865
if I can figure out
a way to make restitution

1242
01:03:45,996 --> 01:03:48,259
for the Wickershams'
transgressions,

1243
01:03:48,389 --> 01:03:50,870
this curse, or this
spirit, whatever it is,

1244
01:03:51,001 --> 01:03:52,611
will give me my George back.

1245
01:03:54,221 --> 01:03:56,223
I'll do whatever I can to help.

1246
01:03:59,879 --> 01:04:01,576
You don't think it's dangerous

1247
01:04:01,707 --> 01:04:03,317
for me to stay
out there, do you?

1248
01:04:03,448 --> 01:04:04,841
The legend says

1249
01:04:04,971 --> 01:04:07,191
that the curse
is tied to the bloodline.

1250
01:04:07,321 --> 01:04:09,584
But I'm not
a Wickersham by birth.

1251
01:04:09,715 --> 01:04:12,152
Your instincts
are better than mine.

1252
01:04:12,283 --> 01:04:15,242
I don't question them,
and I don't think you should.

1253
01:04:20,857 --> 01:04:21,988
[ Engine starting ]

1254
01:04:35,480 --> 01:04:36,873
Where's the hammer?

1255
01:04:46,491 --> 01:04:48,623
No, no! No, no!

1256
01:04:48,754 --> 01:04:50,451
Hello? Hello?

1257
01:05:05,031 --> 01:05:07,033
Come on, Nicky. Where are you?

1258
01:05:07,164 --> 01:05:08,426
[ Ringing ]

1259
01:05:13,692 --> 01:05:15,781
I don't know.
She must not have it with her.

1260
01:05:15,912 --> 01:05:18,566
No biggie. She's probably
already back from the island.

1261
01:05:18,697 --> 01:05:20,394
We'll check around
town when we get there.

1262
01:05:25,443 --> 01:05:26,487
[ Grunts ]

1263
01:05:31,840 --> 01:05:33,059
No, no.

1264
01:05:33,190 --> 01:05:35,235
Don't do it!
Don't do it,

1265
01:05:35,366 --> 01:05:36,541
don't do it!

1266
01:05:36,671 --> 01:05:37,542
[ Sobbing ]

1267
01:06:10,879 --> 01:06:12,316
Oh, my lands!

1268
01:06:16,276 --> 01:06:18,017
[ Thumping, creaking ]

1269
01:06:19,410 --> 01:06:20,237
Is somebody there?

1270
01:06:22,413 --> 01:06:23,544
[ Creaking ]

1271
01:06:28,027 --> 01:06:29,246
No!

1272
01:06:34,512 --> 01:06:35,600
[ Creaking ]

1273
01:06:37,080 --> 01:06:38,298
[ Sniffling ]

1274
01:06:39,952 --> 01:06:41,127
[ Woman wailing ]

1275
01:06:41,258 --> 01:06:42,128
[ Gasps ]

1276
01:06:45,610 --> 01:06:46,872
Who's there?

1277
01:06:49,005 --> 01:06:50,441
[ Woman wailing ]

1278
01:06:50,571 --> 01:06:52,878
Is somebody there?
Who's there?

1279
01:06:57,143 --> 01:06:58,405
[ Wailing ]

1280
01:06:58,536 --> 01:06:59,754
[ Screams ]

1281
01:07:00,973 --> 01:07:03,019
What are you doing in here?

1282
01:07:04,368 --> 01:07:05,934
I was just...

1283
01:07:06,065 --> 01:07:08,720
looking for a hammer,
and the door shut on me!

1284
01:07:10,461 --> 01:07:13,420
It looks like somebody
locked it from out here.

1285
01:07:14,987 --> 01:07:17,076
That's impossible.
I was the only one here.

1286
01:07:22,516 --> 01:07:24,649
It was so dark in there.

1287
01:07:24,779 --> 01:07:27,260
I think it just started
to mess with my mind.

1288
01:07:29,219 --> 01:07:31,264
I swear to you,
I started to hear voices!

1289
01:07:31,395 --> 01:07:33,049
What kind of voices?

1290
01:07:33,179 --> 01:07:36,443
Margie, it was like
there was a woman weeping,

1291
01:07:36,574 --> 01:07:39,490
like, crying or pleading
for help or something.

1292
01:07:39,620 --> 01:07:41,622
Oh! God, I would have
totally freaked out.

1293
01:07:41,753 --> 01:07:42,884
Where were you?

1294
01:07:43,015 --> 01:07:44,843
I thought you'd
gonna be back sooner.

1295
01:07:44,973 --> 01:07:47,454
We tried to call your cell,
but you didn't pick up!

1296
01:07:47,585 --> 01:07:51,023
Peter wanted to show me some
of the sights of Shoal Harbour.

1297
01:07:51,154 --> 01:07:52,633
Is that right?

1298
01:07:52,764 --> 01:07:54,244
- Mm-hmm.
- And how were they?

1299
01:07:54,374 --> 01:07:55,680
We didn't make it past

1300
01:07:55,810 --> 01:07:58,248
the high school
make-out spot, Baker's Bluff.

1301
01:07:58,378 --> 01:08:00,250
The guy has got
a PhD in kissing.

1302
01:08:00,380 --> 01:08:01,512
[ Chuckles ]

1303
01:08:03,340 --> 01:08:04,602
Nicky, I...

1304
01:08:04,732 --> 01:08:06,473
I hate to bail on you,

1305
01:08:06,604 --> 01:08:08,040
but I have to be in Boston

1306
01:08:08,171 --> 01:08:10,086
for a meeting the
day after tomorrow.

1307
01:08:10,216 --> 01:08:12,349
My agent just called
me this afternoon.

1308
01:08:12,479 --> 01:08:13,654
Sorry.

1309
01:08:13,785 --> 01:08:15,439
Of course! No, no.

1310
01:08:15,569 --> 01:08:18,485
Yeah, I get it. I totally
understand. It's fine.

1311
01:08:18,616 --> 01:08:21,140
I'm leaving in the morning.
Why don't you come with me?

1312
01:08:21,271 --> 01:08:23,186
I hate the idea of you
going there alone.

1313
01:08:23,316 --> 01:08:26,276
It's fine! I could just have
Peter stay until you get back.

1314
01:08:26,406 --> 01:08:29,192
Yeah, I hate that even more.

1315
01:08:29,322 --> 01:08:30,149
[ Laughing ]

1316
01:08:31,629 --> 01:08:33,152
What about this curse thing?

1317
01:08:33,283 --> 01:08:34,110
If there's anything

1318
01:08:34,240 --> 01:08:35,633
to it, I just...

1319
01:08:35,763 --> 01:08:38,940
The curse is against
the Wickersham bloodline,

1320
01:08:39,071 --> 01:08:41,465
and George is in Boston,

1321
01:08:41,595 --> 01:08:43,031
so I'll be fine.

1322
01:08:43,162 --> 01:08:44,859
Come here.

1323
01:08:54,913 --> 01:08:57,176
[Man]: I'm simply
a merchant dealing in goods.

1324
01:08:57,307 --> 01:08:59,613
These people are savages

1325
01:08:59,744 --> 01:09:01,963
taken from jungles
and put in homes.

1326
01:09:03,965 --> 01:09:06,359
How bad can it be for them?

1327
01:09:06,490 --> 01:09:10,581
I'm reluctant, but
they offer so much money,

1328
01:09:10,711 --> 01:09:11,756
I can't say no.

1329
01:09:16,674 --> 01:09:17,762
[ Sighs ]

1330
01:09:18,893 --> 01:09:21,461
I know it's wrong,

1331
01:09:21,592 --> 01:09:24,812
but the woman moves me
like no other.

1332
01:09:26,162 --> 01:09:28,338
She is called Kimmika,

1333
01:09:28,468 --> 01:09:30,296
the daughter of a king,

1334
01:09:30,427 --> 01:09:34,518
and she rouses
the most basic passion in me.

1335
01:09:36,128 --> 01:09:38,086
I want to own her

1336
01:09:38,217 --> 01:09:41,264
as much as I want
her to want me.

1337
01:09:41,394 --> 01:09:42,569
[ Phone ringing ]

1338
01:09:44,832 --> 01:09:46,399
Hello?

1339
01:09:46,530 --> 01:09:48,793
Nicky, this is Dr. Burke.
How are you feeling?

1340
01:09:48,923 --> 01:09:50,490
Good! Very good, actually.

1341
01:09:50,621 --> 01:09:52,449
Haven't felt faint
since I've been here.

1342
01:09:52,579 --> 01:09:54,146
Hope you're not
calling with bad news.

1343
01:09:54,277 --> 01:09:55,887
I am calling with news.

1344
01:09:56,017 --> 01:09:57,932
We just got your
blood tests back,

1345
01:09:58,063 --> 01:10:00,152
and it looks like
you're pregnant.

1346
01:10:02,850 --> 01:10:04,112
Nicky?

1347
01:10:04,243 --> 01:10:05,375
Are you there?

1348
01:10:06,680 --> 01:10:08,682
Uh, yeah! Yeah, I...

1349
01:10:08,813 --> 01:10:10,945
Now, you'll have to
come in for a check-up,

1350
01:10:11,076 --> 01:10:12,730
and start on pre-natal vitamins.

1351
01:10:14,210 --> 01:10:15,559
Are you sure?

1352
01:10:15,689 --> 01:10:19,258
100%. You're pregnant!

1353
01:10:19,389 --> 01:10:21,217
Congratulations!

1354
01:10:35,231 --> 01:10:37,015
Is it a boy or a girl?

1355
01:10:37,145 --> 01:10:38,625
I don't know yet.
It's too soon

1356
01:10:38,756 --> 01:10:39,974
to tell.

1357
01:10:40,105 --> 01:10:41,889
What do you want?
Boy or a girl?

1358
01:10:43,500 --> 01:10:45,153
I want...

1359
01:10:47,504 --> 01:10:50,898
...to be able to share
whatever it is with George.

1360
01:10:52,683 --> 01:10:53,901
[ Machine beeping ]

1361
01:10:59,124 --> 01:11:00,691
I just want it to be healthy.

1362
01:11:02,649 --> 01:11:04,172
I wish you would come with me.

1363
01:11:04,303 --> 01:11:06,000
I'm gonna be fine, Margie.

1364
01:11:06,131 --> 01:11:08,220
I just need to...

1365
01:11:08,351 --> 01:11:12,442
figure out the mystery
behind this Wickersham curse,

1366
01:11:12,572 --> 01:11:14,879
and then I'll be back
in Boston the very next day.

1367
01:11:15,009 --> 01:11:16,315
OK.

1368
01:11:16,446 --> 01:11:17,403
[ Phone ringing ]

1369
01:11:17,534 --> 01:11:18,622
Sorry.

1370
01:11:18,752 --> 01:11:20,276
Hello?

1371
01:11:20,406 --> 01:11:23,148
Nicky, I made a print
off your glass plate.

1372
01:11:23,279 --> 01:11:24,715
I think you should see this.

1373
01:11:24,845 --> 01:11:26,412
I'm just at
the caf with Margie.

1374
01:11:26,543 --> 01:11:28,327
I can be there in a few minutes.

1375
01:11:28,458 --> 01:11:31,809
I'll put on a fresh pot
of coffee. Just come right in.

1376
01:11:31,939 --> 01:11:35,160
Considering the age, we're
lucky it's as clear as it is.

1377
01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:37,554
I made the enlargement
so as to get a better look

1378
01:11:37,684 --> 01:11:38,598
at the details.

1379
01:11:38,729 --> 01:11:40,470
Oh, it's amazing.

1380
01:11:40,600 --> 01:11:43,864
Do you recognize the building
she's standing in front of?

1381
01:11:43,995 --> 01:11:46,214
It's the servants'
quarters on the island.

1382
01:11:46,345 --> 01:11:48,129
Right.

1383
01:11:48,260 --> 01:11:50,262
I wonder who she is.

1384
01:11:50,393 --> 01:11:51,916
Hmm! It's anybody's guess.

1385
01:11:54,179 --> 01:11:55,659
There's something
else I want you

1386
01:11:55,789 --> 01:11:57,748
to have a look at. Right there.

1387
01:12:01,229 --> 01:12:02,143
Oh my God.

1388
01:12:02,274 --> 01:12:04,189
It's the brooch.

1389
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:06,191
It's the Wickersham
family brooch.

1390
01:12:06,322 --> 01:12:07,540
It certainly is.

1391
01:12:07,671 --> 01:12:09,107
Why is that a big deal?

1392
01:12:09,237 --> 01:12:10,804
Maybe she was
a Mrs. Wickersham.

1393
01:12:12,284 --> 01:12:13,459
It's Kimmika.

1394
01:12:13,590 --> 01:12:14,895
Who?

1395
01:12:15,026 --> 01:12:16,941
She's an African princess

1396
01:12:17,071 --> 01:12:18,943
that Jebidiah wrote
about in his ledger.

1397
01:12:20,553 --> 01:12:22,163
I need to get
back to the island.

1398
01:12:22,294 --> 01:12:23,164
Whoa!

1399
01:12:23,295 --> 01:12:24,905
Whoa, hold on!

1400
01:12:25,036 --> 01:12:26,603
I think this is getting a little

1401
01:12:26,733 --> 01:12:28,648
too complicated for
someone in your condition.

1402
01:12:28,779 --> 01:12:30,084
Margie.

1403
01:12:30,215 --> 01:12:31,303
[ Sighs ]

1404
01:12:31,434 --> 01:12:32,696
You're pregnant?

1405
01:12:32,826 --> 01:12:34,350
I just found out.

1406
01:12:36,613 --> 01:12:38,876
Certain crystals
are charged with an energy

1407
01:12:39,006 --> 01:12:40,443
that is directly in tune

1408
01:12:40,573 --> 01:12:41,966
with a person's life force.

1409
01:12:42,096 --> 01:12:43,750
And that energy
can be tapped into

1410
01:12:43,881 --> 01:12:45,709
if one understands
the power of it.

1411
01:12:45,839 --> 01:12:46,971
You think that crystal

1412
01:12:47,101 --> 01:12:48,755
call tell the sex
of an unborn child?

1413
01:12:48,886 --> 01:12:50,714
The energy of the child

1414
01:12:50,844 --> 01:12:52,716
and the energy of
the crystal will interact,

1415
01:12:52,846 --> 01:12:54,544
causing it to spin.

1416
01:12:54,674 --> 01:12:57,198
Clockwise for a boy,
counter-clockwise for a girl.

1417
01:12:57,329 --> 01:12:58,504
What if it's both?

1418
01:12:58,635 --> 01:12:59,810
Shh!

1419
01:13:24,791 --> 01:13:26,402
Clockwise.

1420
01:13:27,968 --> 01:13:29,622
It's a boy.

1421
01:13:31,494 --> 01:13:33,409
Oh Nicky, it's wonderful!

1422
01:13:33,539 --> 01:13:35,889
[Sobbing]: No, it's not!

1423
01:13:36,020 --> 01:13:37,369
What are you talking about?

1424
01:13:37,500 --> 01:13:39,110
It's a Wickersham!

1425
01:13:39,240 --> 01:13:40,938
He's the last of the bloodline.

1426
01:13:41,068 --> 01:13:42,983
You're afraid of the curse.

1427
01:13:43,114 --> 01:13:45,072
But the baby's not born yet.

1428
01:13:45,203 --> 01:13:48,380
I mean, how can the curse
possibly know it's a boy?

1429
01:13:50,861 --> 01:13:52,166
I could be wrong!

1430
01:13:54,517 --> 01:13:56,083
[ Phone ringing ]

1431
01:14:01,262 --> 01:14:02,438
Hello?

1432
01:14:02,568 --> 01:14:04,135
Hey Nicky, it's Peter.

1433
01:14:04,265 --> 01:14:06,833
Listen, I'm not gonna
make it out there tonight,

1434
01:14:06,964 --> 01:14:08,922
so there's no need
to come pick me up.

1435
01:14:09,053 --> 01:14:10,141
What's the problem?

1436
01:14:10,271 --> 01:14:11,795
There's a storm coming,

1437
01:14:11,925 --> 01:14:14,798
and I gotta get this roof
patched before it hits.

1438
01:14:14,928 --> 01:14:16,756
OK, I'll meet you
at the dock at 9:00.

1439
01:14:16,887 --> 01:14:19,019
- I'll give you the keys.
- 9:00 it is.

1440
01:14:19,150 --> 01:14:21,587
Lock it up out there tonight.
It's gonna be a rough one.

1441
01:14:22,762 --> 01:14:24,503
Yeah, OK. Bye.

1442
01:14:34,948 --> 01:14:36,602
[ Sighs ]

1443
01:14:47,395 --> 01:14:49,310
The idea of owning her

1444
01:14:49,441 --> 01:14:52,792
fills me with passion
I can barely contain.

1445
01:14:52,923 --> 01:14:55,099
I will log her
"died in transit,"

1446
01:14:55,229 --> 01:14:56,927
then take her home.

1447
01:14:57,057 --> 01:15:00,191
The house for the servants
I plan to employ

1448
01:15:00,321 --> 01:15:02,715
will be where I keep her

1449
01:15:02,846 --> 01:15:06,023
until she offers herself to me
of her own free will.

1450
01:15:14,248 --> 01:15:16,468
Kimmika refuses my advances.

1451
01:15:16,599 --> 01:15:18,949
It's her proud heritage
as the daughter of a king.

1452
01:15:20,603 --> 01:15:22,648
My wife has
discovered my secret,

1453
01:15:22,779 --> 01:15:25,477
and left me no choice
but to kill Kimmika.

1454
01:15:30,177 --> 01:15:31,962
Oh, no, no! Not tonight.

1455
01:15:32,092 --> 01:15:33,311
Not tonight!

1456
01:15:46,324 --> 01:15:47,978
[ Clinking ]

1457
01:15:57,422 --> 01:15:58,641
[ Gasps ]

1458
01:16:03,776 --> 01:16:04,777
[ Grunting ]

1459
01:16:04,908 --> 01:16:05,778
Oh God!

1460
01:16:14,657 --> 01:16:16,223
[ Grunting ]

1461
01:16:30,368 --> 01:16:31,456
OK, OK.

1462
01:16:38,028 --> 01:16:39,290
[ Sobbing ]

1463
01:16:43,033 --> 01:16:43,903
[ Gasps ]

1464
01:16:52,912 --> 01:16:53,870
[ Banging ]

1465
01:16:58,657 --> 01:16:59,789
[ Gasps ]

1466
01:17:03,662 --> 01:17:04,620
[ Gasps ]

1467
01:17:10,408 --> 01:17:11,452
[ Gasps ]

1468
01:17:25,075 --> 01:17:26,250
[ Woman wailing ]

1469
01:17:34,388 --> 01:17:35,738
[ Grunting ]

1470
01:17:42,222 --> 01:17:43,310
[ Grunting ]

1471
01:17:47,967 --> 01:17:49,186
[ Screaming ]

1472
01:17:54,408 --> 01:17:55,540
[ Screaming ]

1473
01:18:00,763 --> 01:18:01,677
[ Grunting ]

1474
01:18:19,607 --> 01:18:21,435
She was brought here as a slave.

1475
01:18:21,566 --> 01:18:23,960
I think that the curse is tied

1476
01:18:24,090 --> 01:18:26,310
to the necklace
she's wearing somehow.

1477
01:18:26,440 --> 01:18:28,312
Your instinct may be right.

1478
01:18:28,442 --> 01:18:31,750
This brooch is
a symbol of royalty

1479
01:18:31,881 --> 01:18:33,752
to a number of African tribes.

1480
01:18:33,883 --> 01:18:36,929
Well, he wrote
that she was a princess.

1481
01:18:37,060 --> 01:18:40,716
Well, then this is the
equivalent of the crown jewels,

1482
01:18:40,846 --> 01:18:43,153
with tremendous
value to the family.

1483
01:18:43,283 --> 01:18:45,808
Valuable enough that
it would allow her spirit

1484
01:18:45,938 --> 01:18:48,636
to seek revenge
if it were stolen?

1485
01:18:48,767 --> 01:18:49,942
[ Scoffs ]

1486
01:18:50,073 --> 01:18:51,988
I'm an anthropologist,
not a spiritualist.

1487
01:18:53,206 --> 01:18:56,079
But if I were so disposed,

1488
01:18:56,209 --> 01:18:58,124
I would think that the emotion

1489
01:18:58,255 --> 01:19:00,736
tied to such a powerful
piece of jewellery

1490
01:19:00,866 --> 01:19:01,911
would lend itself

1491
01:19:02,041 --> 01:19:04,000
to revenge at any cost.

1492
01:19:06,132 --> 01:19:08,482
I need your help, George.

1493
01:19:08,613 --> 01:19:11,485
The curse that's haunted your
family is now our son's legacy.

1494
01:19:12,704 --> 01:19:14,445
Kimmika's hatred allows her

1495
01:19:14,575 --> 01:19:17,230
to cross beyond her world
into this one.

1496
01:19:18,579 --> 01:19:19,885
I know she's holding

1497
01:19:20,016 --> 01:19:21,539
onto you, George.

1498
01:19:21,669 --> 01:19:24,455
I know she's keeping you
from coming back to me.

1499
01:19:27,110 --> 01:19:28,807
I need to break this curse.

1500
01:19:28,938 --> 01:19:31,157
I need to end it for you,

1501
01:19:31,288 --> 01:19:32,680
and for our son.

1502
01:19:34,508 --> 01:19:36,815
But I need your
love to guide me.

1503
01:19:41,994 --> 01:19:43,169
[ Sighs ]

1504
01:19:43,300 --> 01:19:45,302
I can't do this on my own.

1505
01:20:09,152 --> 01:20:11,850
He strangled her
with his bare hands,

1506
01:20:11,981 --> 01:20:14,157
and then he buried her
on the island somewhere.

1507
01:20:14,287 --> 01:20:15,636
Oh, my lands!

1508
01:20:15,767 --> 01:20:18,988
I've been researching
afterlife activity,

1509
01:20:19,118 --> 01:20:21,338
and what would cause
a spirit to haunt a house.

1510
01:20:21,468 --> 01:20:23,296
Every source that I've read

1511
01:20:23,427 --> 01:20:25,559
says that a violent
or tragic death

1512
01:20:25,690 --> 01:20:27,344
would cause the victim
to stay here.

1513
01:20:27,474 --> 01:20:28,998
I'd say this qualifies!

1514
01:20:29,128 --> 01:20:30,651
They're not all malevolent,

1515
01:20:30,782 --> 01:20:33,437
but I would say that
his treatment of Kimmika

1516
01:20:33,567 --> 01:20:35,178
would certainly
justify her rage.

1517
01:20:35,308 --> 01:20:37,049
Listen to me, Nicky.

1518
01:20:37,180 --> 01:20:40,313
There are no guarantees
in the spirit world.

1519
01:20:40,444 --> 01:20:43,360
You've got to leave this
place, and never come back!

1520
01:20:44,840 --> 01:20:46,406
I can't do that.

1521
01:20:47,668 --> 01:20:49,018
I can't risk losing my baby.

1522
01:20:50,846 --> 01:20:52,891
You could lose
his life and yours

1523
01:20:53,022 --> 01:20:54,719
if you go back to that island!

1524
01:20:54,850 --> 01:20:56,634
And the history of that family

1525
01:20:56,764 --> 01:20:59,376
would indicate that that's
the most popular outcome.

1526
01:20:59,506 --> 01:21:01,291
Do you understand that?

1527
01:21:02,814 --> 01:21:05,164
It's not something
I want to do, Virginia.

1528
01:21:05,295 --> 01:21:07,732
It's something I have to do
for my husband and my son.

1529
01:21:07,863 --> 01:21:09,908
Every instinct I have in my body

1530
01:21:10,039 --> 01:21:12,258
tells me this spirit
has a hold of George.

1531
01:21:12,389 --> 01:21:14,304
He needs me to do this,

1532
01:21:14,434 --> 01:21:16,306
and I'm not gonna
let my fear condemn him.

1533
01:21:16,436 --> 01:21:18,569
This is a very powerful crystal.

1534
01:21:18,699 --> 01:21:22,312
It promotes positive energy
and repels negative energy.

1535
01:21:25,619 --> 01:21:27,273
I'll get it back to you soon.

1536
01:21:27,404 --> 01:21:28,622
[ Engine starting ]

1537
01:22:06,182 --> 01:22:07,792
Where are you, Kimmika?

1538
01:22:24,417 --> 01:22:26,158
Is that an invitation?

1539
01:23:25,348 --> 01:23:26,305
[ Gasps ]

1540
01:24:04,474 --> 01:24:05,649
[ Grunting ]

1541
01:24:16,660 --> 01:24:17,878
[ Gasps ]

1542
01:24:21,012 --> 01:24:22,144
Oh my God!

1543
01:24:28,541 --> 01:24:30,413
Oh my God, she had a baby!

1544
01:24:33,677 --> 01:24:35,635
He killed her and her bloodline.

1545
01:24:58,005 --> 01:24:59,659
Rest in peace, Kimmika.

1546
01:25:01,487 --> 01:25:02,706
I'm so sorry.

1547
01:26:02,287 --> 01:26:03,549
[ Chuckles ]

1548
01:26:10,643 --> 01:26:12,079
Please don't look at it yet.

1549
01:26:12,210 --> 01:26:13,994
It's so bad.

1550
01:26:14,125 --> 01:26:16,214
Well, you're not painting
for me, Bobby-Ann.

1551
01:26:16,345 --> 01:26:17,520
You're painting for you.

1552
01:26:17,650 --> 01:26:19,913
Trust your instincts!

1553
01:26:20,044 --> 01:26:21,915
It's really nice! Keep going.

1554
01:26:22,046 --> 01:26:23,221
Thanks, Nicky!

1555
01:26:23,352 --> 01:26:24,527
Yeah.

1556
01:26:24,657 --> 01:26:26,877
There's Georgie 5, all changed

1557
01:26:27,007 --> 01:26:28,357
with a nice dry diaper.

1558
01:26:28,487 --> 01:26:30,141
Thank you, Auntie Ginny.

1559
01:26:30,272 --> 01:26:31,403
Hi, handsome!

1560
01:26:36,887 --> 01:26:37,844
Hey, baby.

1561
01:26:37,975 --> 01:26:39,106
[ Squeals ]

1562
01:26:39,237 --> 01:26:40,456
Pretty!

1563
01:26:42,762 --> 01:26:44,677
Thank you!

1564
01:26:44,808 --> 01:26:46,766
Oh, this came for you yesterday,

1565
01:26:46,897 --> 01:26:48,551
but I wanted to give
it to you myself.

1566
01:26:48,681 --> 01:26:50,683
What brings you out?

1567
01:26:50,814 --> 01:26:53,338
I heard you guys were
having a symposium out here.

1568
01:26:53,469 --> 01:26:55,297
Do you even know
what that means?

1569
01:26:55,427 --> 01:26:57,560
It's the Greek word
for a drinking party.

1570
01:26:57,690 --> 01:26:58,778
I got it!

1571
01:26:58,909 --> 01:27:00,519
- What?
- It's the grant cheque

1572
01:27:00,650 --> 01:27:03,827
for the Wickersham Island
Summer Artists' Retreat.

1573
01:27:03,957 --> 01:27:05,481
Yes! Nice!

1574
01:27:05,611 --> 01:27:07,004
Let me see it!

1575
01:27:07,134 --> 01:27:09,572
Well, I think we
should have a symposium.

1576
01:27:09,702 --> 01:27:11,008
Yes, we should.

1577
01:27:13,140 --> 01:27:14,794
You are amazing.

1578
01:27:14,925 --> 01:27:17,406
Not only do you
turn a haunted island

1579
01:27:17,536 --> 01:27:19,190
into a haunt
for starving artists,

1580
01:27:19,321 --> 01:27:21,192
but you saved my life.

1581
01:27:21,323 --> 01:27:23,586
Not bad for a woman who
had to find the courage

1582
01:27:23,716 --> 01:27:25,414
to show her own art.

1583
01:27:25,544 --> 01:27:27,546
Well, I'd rather take on

1584
01:27:27,677 --> 01:27:30,854
an angry ghost than
a jaded art critic any day.

1585
01:27:30,984 --> 01:27:32,247
[ George chuckles ]

